<a name="2404"></a>

<div class="sub-content-header">Another Record Crowd at the Seventh Annual Exhibitor Workshop </div>
<br />

<IMG height=133 hspace=10 src="/images/photos/Workshop(1).jpg" width=200 align=right vspace=10>The seventh annual CES Exhibitor Workshop drew a record crowd on October 22 at the Las Vegas Convention Center (LVCC)&nbsp;in Las Vegas, Nev.<BR><BR>More than 60 exhibitors were present at this year’s event, which started out with a keynote by Glenda Brungardt, Tradeshow and Event Manager of HP, addressing best practices for tracking your ROI in her presentation "<I>What's Measurement Got To Do With It?</I>"<BR><BR>CEA VP of Sales and Business Development Dan Cole hosted the workshop, which included presentations by Katie Swearingen and Martha Sproehnle on CES operations, Ed Kelter of the Las Vegas Convention Center Security team, and a panel from GES including Mark Munhall, Kevin Gibbs, Martin Laurel, Cyndy Peterson and Bill Palubinsky.<BR><BR>A new feature for this year's workshop was the CES Power Hour. During the Power Hour session, attendees heard presentations from Michelle Griffin on free CES marketing tools, Allison Carney with public relations tips, the GES team on freight and drayage, Katie Swearingen on how to utilize the Exhibitor Manual and Liz Tardif on CES promotional opportunities.<BR><BR>Exhibitors visited the CES vendor fair, spoke one on one with more than 20 vendors and got the inside scoop on&nbsp;CES SmartBooth, powered by BDMetrics. In the afternoon, attendees were treated to an expert panel Q&amp;A session. The panel was made up of Howie Cooperstein of Bell'O International Corp, Laura Leeper of Cisco and Allen Reichard of AMD. The day wrapped up with&nbsp;tours of both the LVCC and Sands/Venetian exhibit space.<BR><BR>If you missed the workshop or want to experience it again, check out the workshop webcast which will be available soon&nbsp;on <A href="/exhibitors/resources/workshop.asp">Exhibitor Workshop homepage</A>.
        <br /><img width="1" height="20" src="/images/framework/spacer.gif"/>
        <img height="15" alt="" src="/images/framework/divider-line.gif"/><br />

<a name="2402"></a>

<div class="sub-content-header">Industry Insider Series at CES</div>
<br />

Get the inside view of the digital economy from the people who are shaping it! These <A href="/sessions/default.asp">free sessions</A> put you in touch with dynamic entrepreneurs, inventors and visionaries who share their experiences and perspectives.<BR><BR>All <A href="/sessions/default.asp">Industry Insiders</A> will be held in the Las Vegas Hilton Theater.<BR><BR><IMG src="/images/photos/Industry_Insiders_copy.jpg">&nbsp;<BR><BR><STRONG>Dirk Meyer</STRONG>, AMD President and CEO - 11 a.m., January 8 <BR><STRONG>Anne Sweeney</STRONG>, Disney Media Networks Co-chair and Disney-ABC Television Group President - 2:30 p.m., January 8 <BR><STRONG>Michael Griffith</STRONG>, Activision Publishing President and CEO - 11 a.m., January 9
        <br /><img width="1" height="20" src="/images/framework/spacer.gif"/>
        <img height="15" alt="" src="/images/framework/divider-line.gif"/><br />

<a name="2455"></a>

<div class="sub-content-header">Innovation Honorees to be Announced in New York</div>
<br />

<IMG height=142 hspace=10 src="/images/content/innov2009.jpg" width=95 align=right>Lots of ideas make it off the drawing board. Only the best make it to Innovations. <BR><BR>The Innovations 2009 Design and Engineering Awards program recognizes the most innovative consumer electronics (CE) products in the industry's hottest product categories. This year's Innovations Honorees will be revealed in New York at the 2009 International CES Press Preview on November 11, 2009.<BR><BR>The best-of-the-best in 34 product categories, with the power to inspire and amaze. You may not have thought of it, but you'll be glad someone did.
        <br /><img width="1" height="20" src="/images/framework/spacer.gif"/>
        <img height="15" alt="" src="/images/framework/divider-line.gif"/><br />

<a name="2400"></a>

<div class="sub-content-header">Visa Application Process</div>
<br />

If you are an exhibitor that requires a Visa to enter the U.S., request your letter of invitation and make your appointment for a visa interview early. Wait times for a visa interview can be several weeks or more in many countries, especially during peak travel periods. With this in mind, we strongly urge you to register for CES and request a letter of invitation as soon as possible. For helpful tips on securing your visa, view our <A href="/international/travel.asp">travel and visa information</A>.
        <br /><img width="1" height="20" src="/images/framework/spacer.gif"/>
        <img height="15" alt="" src="/images/framework/divider-line.gif"/><br />

<a name="2399"></a>

<div class="sub-content-header">Exhibitor PR/IR Contact Information</div>
<br />

<I>Leverage CES PR tools before, during and after the 2009 International CES by sending us your PR contact information.</I> <BR><BR>To ensure that the media can find you at CES, make sure to list your company's PR contact. We will direct any media inquiries we receive regarding your company or products to the individual you indicate. The contact information will be available to all registered CES media. Go to your <A href="https://myces.bdmetrics.com/exhibitorportal/EventLogin.aspx">MyCES Exhibitor</A><A href="https://myces.bdmetrics.com/exhibitorportal/EventLogin.aspx"> Portal</A> to add/update your PR contact information. <BR><BR>Questions? Contact Allison Carney at acarney@CE.org.
        <br /><img width="1" height="20" src="/images/framework/spacer.gif"/>
        <img height="15" alt="" src="/images/framework/divider-line.gif"/><br />

<a name="2398"></a>

<div class="sub-content-header">Exhibitor PR Newsletter</div>
<br />

The <A href="/exhibitors/pr/exhibitorPRnl.asp">Exhibitor PR Newsletter</A> is a monthly distribution designed to help you keep your public relations efforts in check with valuable tips, deadline reminders and breaking news. Check it out to see the latest CES press events and discover ways to maximize your company's media exposure all year long. By <A href="https://myces.bdmetrics.com/exhibitorportal/EventLogin.aspx" target=_blank>registering</A>, your PR contact will receive these important CES news tips on the first Wednesday of every month. <BR><BR>The newsletter is also posted on CESweb.org on the second Wednesday of the month, after all registered contacts have had the opportunity to receive it electronically.
