    <p><strong>Extend Your Brand Virtually with CES Online Advertising</strong><br> by Dan Cole</p>
    <p>With Thanksgiving quickly approaching and Christmas and Hanukkah less than eight weeks away, it can only mean that the 2009 International CES is right around the corner! In an increasingly competitive marketplace, the International CES is the one event where you can maximize your marketing dollars and networking opportunities, so get ready!<BR><BR>Trade show exhibitors have traditionally banked their success solely on their ability to secure an optimal physical presence at the event itself. After the booth aesthetics are finalized, as in real estate, the rallying cry is "location, location, location!" Staking a prime location near an entrance or a major company with significant traffic is important to most.&nbsp; For some, positioning their booth away from a direct competitor is a priority, while others prefer to “keep their enemies close.” Whatever the objective, the booth remains the epicenter of most company’s trade show participation strategy.&nbsp; <BR><BR>But, advertising and marketing strategies are changing. The internet has emerged as a key tool in extending brand to maximum audiences. And with the emergence of social networks such as Facebook, Twitter and Digg, the viral spread of your brand offers limitless opportunities. These new media vehicles can help make your "virtual" trade show presence just as powerful as your physical one.&nbsp; <BR><BR>Did you know that between December and February, the <A href="http://www.CESweb.org" target=_blank>CESweb.org</A> homepage receives over 1 million unique hits?&nbsp; The professionals who visit this page are key influencers and decision-makers in the CE industry, and the ones you want to connect with. A featured ad on the <A href="http://www.CESweb.org" target=_blank>CESweb.org</A> homepage, or on the landing page for your particular product category, is a great way to reach this targeted audience.</p>
    <!-- article end -->
